<i>I'll cook today's dish quickly.</i>

263
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:21,500
CHEF JIN-SEONG

264
00:24:21,585 --> 00:24:23,665
<i>Please stay tuned
to see if I'll be able...</i>

265
00:24:50,280 --> 00:24:52,530
Among the stories you sent me,

266
00:24:52,616 --> 00:24:55,286
-I think the second one's the best.
-I see.

267
00:24:55,368 --> 00:24:56,908
-We should select it.
-I agree.

268
00:24:56,995 --> 00:24:58,705
-Hi, Chef Park.
-Hello.

269
00:25:08,173 --> 00:25:09,973
Hi, Chef Park.

270
00:25:10,467 --> 00:25:11,377
Hi.

271
00:25:15,096 --> 00:25:16,886
Have you been well?

272
00:25:23,230 --> 00:25:24,400
Hi, Chef Park.

273
00:25:25,148 --> 00:25:25,978
Chef Park?

274
00:25:29,486 --> 00:25:32,066
By the way, I guess you two haven't seen
each other for a while.

275
00:25:35,784 --> 00:25:39,084
I've been too busy
to go to the bistro often lately.

276
00:25:39,579 --> 00:25:41,119
Gosh, that's a pity.

277
00:25:42,874 --> 00:25:45,294
All right. Shall we begin
the meeting then?

278
00:25:45,377 --> 00:25:46,377
-Sure.
-Sure.

279
00:25:47,629 --> 00:25:51,679
Mr. Nam, I think we'll really end up
going on vacation abroad at this rate.

280
00:25:52,634 --> 00:25:54,974
The director promised a bonus
if we get 10 percent,

281
00:25:55,053 --> 00:25:57,563
and a trip abroad if we get 15 percent,
you know.

282
00:26:11,111 --> 00:26:12,401
What's wrong?

283
00:26:16,032 --> 00:26:18,832
-Isn't that Park Jin-seong?
-Oh, you're right.

284
00:26:18,910 --> 00:26:20,700
-Hey, take a picture.
-I'll go to the bathroom.

285
00:26:20,787 --> 00:26:22,787
-You guys go ahead.
-Okay.

286
00:26:22,872 --> 00:26:23,922
Wait.

287
00:26:27,919 --> 00:26:30,209
What are you doing here?

288
00:26:30,297 --> 00:26:31,587
Why are you here?

289
00:26:33,091 --> 00:26:35,391
I'm having an audition for <i>Changing You.</i>

290
00:26:35,468 --> 00:26:36,888
Jin-u.

291
00:26:36,970 --> 00:26:40,140
I know what you're worried about.

292
00:26:40,223 --> 00:26:42,433
It's really hard to pass the audition,

293
00:26:43,018 --> 00:26:45,688
and I'm not sure if I'll pass,
so I didn't tell you.

294
00:26:46,313 --> 00:26:48,273
-I can't let you be on TV.
-Jin-seong.

295
00:26:49,232 --> 00:26:51,112
This is a really big opportunity for me.

296
00:26:51,860 --> 00:26:54,320
I want to know how capable I am.

297
00:26:54,404 --> 00:26:56,324
Still, I can't let you be on a TV show.

298
00:26:56,406 --> 00:26:58,276
-Why not?
-Do you really have to ask?

299
00:26:58,366 --> 00:27:00,906
Why do I have to give up because of you?

300
00:27:01,536 --> 00:27:03,906
This is my life,
and it's a good opportunity for me.

301
00:27:07,083 --> 00:27:08,963
-Jin-u.
-I'll make sure no one finds out.

302
00:27:09,753 --> 00:27:11,423
If people find out I lied,

303
00:27:12,255 --> 00:27:13,665
you'll suffer from it too.

304
00:27:15,133 --> 00:27:17,933
Suffering from that later
and suffering from giving up now,

305
00:27:18,011 --> 00:27:19,141
they're the same to me.

306
00:27:19,721 --> 00:27:22,221
I can't hide for the rest of my life
because of your lie.

307
00:27:25,226 --> 00:27:28,016
I got to go now. I have an interview.

308
00:27:54,005 --> 00:27:55,415
Hi, guys.

309
00:28:02,263 --> 00:28:03,143
Hey, Chef Park.

310
00:28:04,974 --> 00:28:06,064
-Hello.
-Hi.

311
00:28:06,142 --> 00:28:08,692
Your bistro must be so busy
thanks to <i>Sweet Munchies</i>, right?

312
00:28:09,687 --> 00:28:11,607
-Right.
-I'll come by one of these days

313
00:28:11,689 --> 00:28:13,479
and order a ton to help you out, okay?

314
00:28:14,317 --> 00:28:15,987
-Okay.
-Have a nice day.

315
00:28:16,069 --> 00:28:17,779
-Let's go, <i>Sweet Munchies!</i>
-Thanks.

316
00:28:17,862 --> 00:28:18,702
Keep up the good work!

317
00:28:22,742 --> 00:28:25,122
-Hello, sir.
-Hi.

318
00:28:30,750 --> 00:28:32,710
What? Nobody picked it up?

319
00:28:37,882 --> 00:28:40,512
Is it because only five numbers
are circled?

320
00:28:42,470 --> 00:28:44,060
Then I should circle one more.

321
00:28:46,516 --> 00:28:49,096
Why are people so scrupulous?

322
00:29:15,170 --> 00:29:17,130
Hi, Jin-u.

323
00:29:17,213 --> 00:29:19,673
I'm so glad to see you here.

324
00:29:19,758 --> 00:29:20,798
Hello.

325
00:29:21,551 --> 00:29:23,851
When I was reviewing the resumes,

326
00:29:23,928 --> 00:29:26,928
I was so surprised to see
your application.

327
00:29:27,015 --> 00:29:30,055
It's like you and your brother are
meant to be on TV.

328
00:29:33,062 --> 00:29:34,812
Well... Anyway,

329
00:29:35,940 --> 00:29:37,860
I don't want people to know

330
00:29:38,902 --> 00:29:41,072
that Jin-seong and I are brothers.

331
00:29:42,405 --> 00:29:44,405
Sure. I got it.

332
00:29:45,325 --> 00:29:47,035
The show will never reveal the fact.

333
00:29:47,118 --> 00:29:49,538
-Thank you.
-Jin-u.

334
00:29:50,121 --> 00:29:53,881
I may be quite close to you and Chef Park,

335
00:29:53,958 --> 00:29:58,458
but I draw a very distinct line
between work and personal life.

336
00:29:59,088 --> 00:30:00,338
Of course.

337
00:30:00,423 --> 00:30:02,633
Besides, I want to be recognized
for my own competence.

338
00:30:02,717 --> 00:30:03,967
That's good.

339
00:30:08,014 --> 00:30:10,234
-Hello.
-Hello.

340
00:30:10,308 --> 00:30:13,018
All right, then.
Shall we begin the interview?

341
00:30:13,102 --> 00:30:14,522
Sure.

342
00:30:18,483 --> 00:30:19,483
Okay.

343
00:30:22,403 --> 00:30:24,913
Let's see what's been filmed.

344
00:30:27,283 --> 00:30:30,453
What? Chef Park was filmed?

345
00:31:17,959 --> 00:31:21,419
But you didn't even call me beforehand.
What's the occasion?

346
00:31:21,504 --> 00:31:24,264
You wouldn't answer my calls,
so I was worried.

347
00:31:24,966 --> 00:31:26,506
You're not sick, are you?

348
00:31:27,343 --> 00:31:31,603
No, I just have been quite busy with work.

349
00:31:36,394 --> 00:31:37,564
You don't have a fever.

350
00:31:39,063 --> 00:31:41,903
-You haven't eaten yet, right?
-No, not yet.

351
00:31:42,567 --> 00:31:44,147
You made it all by yourself?

352
00:31:45,069 --> 00:31:45,899
Of course.

353
00:31:47,113 --> 00:31:48,243
Dig in.

354
00:31:49,616 --> 00:31:50,526
Thank you.

355
00:31:51,910 --> 00:31:53,830
-Thanks for the food.
-Sure.

356
00:32:02,795 --> 00:32:04,085
To tell you the truth,

357
00:32:04,172 --> 00:32:07,472
I had a falling-out with my father
not too long ago.

358
00:32:09,677 --> 00:32:12,967
Turns out it's not easy to go against
a parent once you're an adult.

359
00:32:14,891 --> 00:32:17,311
I knew it. I'm glad I came to see you.

360
00:32:18,061 --> 00:32:18,901
So?

361
00:32:21,230 --> 00:32:24,030
-You want me to dance for you?
-No, thanks.

362
00:32:25,318 --> 00:32:26,398
I'll just eat.

363
00:32:36,537 --> 00:32:38,157
What's that look for?

364
00:32:38,247 --> 00:32:39,367
You have something to tell me?

365
00:32:41,292 --> 00:32:42,962
No, I don't.

366
00:32:43,628 --> 00:32:46,798
Then what's that look on your face?
You look like a dog that needs to go.

367
00:32:48,216 --> 00:32:49,426
Well...

368
00:33:07,360 --> 00:33:08,240
Mr. Lee.

369
00:33:09,904 --> 00:33:11,954
What are you doing here
with all the lights off?

370
00:33:12,031 --> 00:33:13,781
Hey. You haven't gotten off work yet?

371
00:33:13,866 --> 00:33:16,326
No. I'm still doing the editing.

372
00:33:17,578 --> 00:33:18,868
Okay. Keep it up.

373
00:33:19,455 --> 00:33:21,325
-Okay. Good night.
-Good night.

374
00:33:49,444 --> 00:33:50,994
Do you want to join me?

375
00:33:53,990 --> 00:33:56,870
But there's not much to eat.
What do we do?

376
00:33:56,951 --> 00:33:59,081
Should I go buy something?
Or should we order in something?

377
00:33:59,162 --> 00:34:01,162
-No, this is enough.
-Are you sure?

378
00:34:07,712 --> 00:34:10,172
Anyway, I think you're working too hard.

379
00:34:11,466 --> 00:34:12,756
But it's fun.

380
00:34:13,468 --> 00:34:15,678
-Is it fun?
-Yes.

381
00:34:15,762 --> 00:34:19,812
Work is fun,
and I like everyone I work with.

382
00:34:23,019 --> 00:34:25,099
How are you doing with Park Jin-seong?

383
00:34:26,064 --> 00:34:27,194
Pardon?

384
00:34:28,566 --> 00:34:29,726
I mean,

385
00:34:30,902 --> 00:34:32,952
what does he mean to you?

386
00:34:38,159 --> 00:34:40,199
Well...

387
00:34:43,247 --> 00:34:44,537
I feel thankful to him.

388
00:34:46,501 --> 00:34:47,841
I don't know.

389
00:34:49,212 --> 00:34:53,092
It's very hard to describe it
with words, but...

390
00:34:55,635 --> 00:34:56,925
He's like my savior.

391
00:34:58,763 --> 00:35:00,183
When I was having the hardest time,

392
00:35:01,015 --> 00:35:03,345
he appeared at the perfect timing

393
00:35:04,477 --> 00:35:05,977
to save me.

394
00:35:10,066 --> 00:35:10,976
A-jin.

395
00:35:11,692 --> 00:35:12,532
Yes?

396
00:35:18,366 --> 00:35:20,076
What's the matter?

397
00:35:21,119 --> 00:35:24,159
Is there something wrong?

398
00:35:27,416 --> 00:35:29,746
No, nothing's wrong.

399
00:35:31,295 --> 00:35:33,255
Don't skip meals too often.

400
00:35:33,339 --> 00:35:35,549
Your health is what matters most.

401
00:35:53,734 --> 00:35:54,994
All right.

402
00:35:58,114 --> 00:36:02,164
Sweet... No, Nam Gyu-jang.

403
00:36:04,078 --> 00:36:05,408
What nice pictures.

404
00:36:05,997 --> 00:36:08,117
An interview with Nam Gyu-jang...

405
00:36:10,835 --> 00:36:11,665
What?

406
00:36:11,752 --> 00:36:13,962
<i>K DAILY</i>
"CHEF PARK MADE A LOT OF WOMEN CRY"

407
00:36:14,046 --> 00:36:16,046
"CHEF PARK'S COMPLICATED PRIVATE LIFE?"

408
00:36:16,132 --> 00:36:18,052
"IS CHEF PARK REALLY GAY?"

409
00:36:18,718 --> 00:36:19,968
What the hell?

410
00:36:20,803 --> 00:36:22,143
-Mr. Nam.
-Yes?

411
00:36:22,722 --> 00:36:24,102
What are these articles?

412
00:36:26,350 --> 00:36:27,640
Well, it's...

413
00:36:27,727 --> 00:36:29,437
Are you trying to screw up the show?

414
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:31,150
What the hell’s wrong with you?

415
00:36:31,230 --> 00:36:34,650
I just...
I had no idea they'd do this to me.

416
00:36:34,734 --> 00:36:36,614
This is malicious editing.

417
00:36:36,694 --> 00:36:40,244
Are you saying they wrote the article
with something you didn't say?

418
00:36:43,409 --> 00:36:44,829
What are you going to do now?

419
00:36:47,205 --> 00:36:48,245
Answer me!

420
00:36:50,791 --> 00:36:52,211
Whatever. Just go.

421
00:36:52,293 --> 00:36:54,923
Come on, you can't just avoid it!

422
00:36:55,004 --> 00:36:56,134
Keep it down.

423
00:36:58,424 --> 00:37:01,644
Then why don't you call and ask them
to take down the article?

424
00:37:01,719 --> 00:37:03,719
Okay, just give me
the journalist's number.

425
00:37:04,680 --> 00:37:06,100
Give me now.

426
00:37:07,433 --> 00:37:09,273
But they're all true.

427
00:37:09,852 --> 00:37:12,942
As far as I know, you met that woman too.

428
00:37:15,483 --> 00:37:21,113
Yes, but the article sounds like
Chef Park is lying to the viewers.

429
00:37:21,197 --> 00:37:22,027
I don't know.

430
00:37:22,907 --> 00:37:25,157
It's not like I made up the stories.

431
00:37:25,243 --> 00:37:29,293
I don't understand
why you're so upset like this.

432
00:37:30,623 --> 00:37:31,713
Mr. Han.

433
00:37:33,584 --> 00:37:37,554
Have a look at these malicious comments.

434
00:37:37,630 --> 00:37:40,800
If he was afraid of such a thing,
he shouldn't have been on TV.

435
00:37:40,883 --> 00:37:42,973
Besides, he came out of the closet on TV.

436
00:37:46,055 --> 00:37:48,805
If you want to turn
this negativity around,

437
00:37:49,892 --> 00:37:52,732
why don't you have Chef Park
have an exclusive interview?

438
00:37:56,649 --> 00:38:00,319
Don't you have a Code of Ethics
as a journalist?

439
00:38:01,487 --> 00:38:04,197
Whatever happens to a person's reputation,

440
00:38:04,282 --> 00:38:05,622
you're not interested in the truth.

441
00:38:05,700 --> 00:38:08,490
You're only interested
in producing provocative gossip.

442
00:38:08,577 --> 00:38:10,327
And what? "An interview with Chef Park"?

443
00:38:10,913 --> 00:38:14,043
I'll talk him out of it
even if he's willing to do it.

444
00:38:14,125 --> 00:38:17,585
Please issue a correction
to let people know the truth,

445
00:38:17,670 --> 00:38:18,880
or take down the article,

446
00:38:19,463 --> 00:38:22,723
before I sue you for defamation.

447
00:38:36,856 --> 00:38:38,686
<i>SWEET MUNCHIES</i>
"IS HE REALLY GAY?"

448
00:38:42,820 --> 00:38:44,360
A GUY DOING ANOTHER GUY?
THAT'S DISGUSTING.

449
00:38:44,447 --> 00:38:46,117
STOP MAKING IT LOOK LIKE LGBTS ARE VICTIMS

450
00:38:46,198 --> 00:38:47,948
THE SHOW'S PROMOTING
HOMOSEXUALITY. CANCEL IT!

451
00:38:54,999 --> 00:38:57,499
CHEF PARK JIN-SEONG

452
00:39:02,631 --> 00:39:07,221
CHEF PARK JIN-SEONG

453
00:39:26,364 --> 00:39:28,574
JERK!

454
00:39:40,461 --> 00:39:41,461
I'll help you.

455
00:39:42,338 --> 00:39:44,838
-No, it's okay. I can do it.
-No.

456
00:39:44,924 --> 00:39:47,474
YOU'RE DISGUSTING!
JERK!

457
00:40:06,862 --> 00:40:10,372
These are the stories of those
who were comforted thanks to you.

458
00:40:11,283 --> 00:40:16,163
And these are the stories of those
who started a new life, thanks to you.

459
00:40:16,247 --> 00:40:18,577
-And these--
-You don't have to try so hard.

460
00:40:21,377 --> 00:40:23,747
I don't deserve to be consoled by you.

461
00:40:26,298 --> 00:40:27,678
What do you mean?

462
00:40:30,928 --> 00:40:32,178
I'm being punished,

463
00:40:33,806 --> 00:40:34,806
with all this.

464
00:40:43,899 --> 00:40:46,399
I didn't imagine
anything like this would happen.

465
00:40:49,405 --> 00:40:51,235
Whenever you have to make a choice,

466
00:40:53,117 --> 00:40:55,287
you're supposed to think it through

467
00:40:56,036 --> 00:40:58,996
to find the best option,
or at least the second-best,

468
00:41:00,040 --> 00:41:01,830
before you make the choice.

469
00:41:04,712 --> 00:41:06,422
But I was so clueless.

470
00:41:08,257 --> 00:41:09,627
I just wanted to solve

471
00:41:11,051 --> 00:41:12,681
the problem I had...

472
00:41:15,264 --> 00:41:16,354
at that moment.

473
00:41:17,683 --> 00:41:19,353
<i>Why did he say something like that?</i>

474
00:41:26,942 --> 00:41:29,362
Hey, Jae-su. Why don't you

475
00:41:30,738 --> 00:41:32,068
go meet Chef Park?

476
00:41:33,073 --> 00:41:34,123
Me?

477
00:41:34,200 --> 00:41:37,950
I mean, what good will it do us
if his feelings are hurt?

478
00:41:39,330 --> 00:41:41,080
Wait. Here it is.

479
00:41:42,166 --> 00:41:44,496
Here's the company credit card. Take it.

480
00:41:45,002 --> 00:41:49,222
If he seems upset,
use this to make him feel better.

481
00:41:49,298 --> 00:41:51,378
Come on, you need to do it
for him to feel better.

482
00:41:52,593 --> 00:41:55,263
To be blunt, this happened
because of the interview you did.

483
00:41:55,346 --> 00:41:57,346
-You little...
-How could you ask me to do it?

484
00:41:57,431 --> 00:41:58,891
Just go comfort him as I say.

485
00:41:58,974 --> 00:42:00,604
And I have a lot to do
as the main producer.

486
00:42:01,185 --> 00:42:03,055
I'm busy too. I can't do it.

487
00:42:03,812 --> 00:42:06,322
Besides, I don't think I can face him.

488
00:42:06,398 --> 00:42:07,608
You little...

489
00:42:07,691 --> 00:42:12,111
Hey, did you forget
that I'm keeping your secret?

490
00:42:13,155 --> 00:42:14,155
Don't forget that.

491
00:42:16,492 --> 00:42:17,582
Go now.

492
00:42:19,912 --> 00:42:20,832
Oh, right.

493
00:42:21,789 --> 00:42:23,919
Don't spend too much, okay?

494
00:42:23,999 --> 00:42:25,129
Okay.

495
00:42:25,834 --> 00:42:27,634
Whatever you say...

496
00:42:33,050 --> 00:42:36,800
How could he take advantage
of our personal life like that?

497
00:42:36,887 --> 00:42:39,007
We're just hiding it
to work like professionals.

498
00:42:39,098 --> 00:42:41,348
It's not like we're criminals
who killed someone.

499
00:42:42,685 --> 00:42:44,265
Let's just put up with him.

500
00:42:49,692 --> 00:42:51,032
Let's just tell them.

501
00:42:53,195 --> 00:42:54,275
You mean it?

502
00:42:55,281 --> 00:42:56,781
-Is it really okay with you?
-Yes.

503
00:42:57,825 --> 00:43:03,455
And go tell Nam Gyu-jang
that he should clean up his own mess.

504
00:43:07,251 --> 00:43:09,001
You make sure to tell him that.

505
00:43:09,086 --> 00:43:11,296
Or I'll tell him myself,
grabbing him by the collar.

506
00:43:12,548 --> 00:43:13,668
Okay.

507
00:43:16,844 --> 00:43:19,264
What are you doing? Stop it.

508
00:43:20,180 --> 00:43:21,270
Let me hug you once more.

509
00:43:21,348 --> 00:43:23,598
-I'll tell him that.
-You do that.

510
00:43:23,684 --> 00:43:24,734
He's doomed now.

511
00:43:26,645 --> 00:43:27,685
Come on.

512
00:43:29,189 --> 00:43:31,979
<i>There's something I need to tell
our </i>Sweet Munchies<i> team.</i>

513
00:43:32,067 --> 00:43:34,357
<i>Can we all meet at the bistro later?</i>

514
00:44:16,028 --> 00:44:18,238
It smells really delicious.

515
00:44:18,322 --> 00:44:20,122
-Hi.
-Hi.

516
00:44:20,199 --> 00:44:22,619
-Have a seat there, please.
-Okay.

